On-disk format spec (Tier-0 target)
Partitioning model

For Tier-0 owned FAT32, lock this initial policy:

Partition style: MBR

Partition count: 1

Partition type: FAT32 LBA (0x0C)

Alignment: 1 MiB boundary

Partition starts at: LBA 2048

Partition consumes: remainder of disk minus reserved tail if needed

Active flag: false by default

This keeps behavior simple and broadly compatible.

FAT32 profile v1

Initial owned FAT32 profile:

bytes/sector: 512

sectors/cluster:

choose deterministically by volume size

reserved sectors:

standard FAT32 reserved region, deterministic constant

FAT count: 2

root directory cluster: 2

media descriptor: standard removable media value

FSInfo sector: present and valid

backup boot sector: present and valid

volume label:

uppercase

FAT-safe sanitized

max 11 chars

volume serial:

deterministic, not clock-derived

Deterministic cluster sizing rule

Lock a simple first rule:

<= 32 GiB → 16 KiB or 32 KiB

> 32 GiB and <= 512 GiB → 32 KiB

later override possible via explicit parameter

For your immediate use case, 256 GB → 32 KiB clusters.

Deterministic volume serial rule

Do not use current time.

Use deterministic derivation from target facts, for example:

VolumeSerial = first 4 bytes of SHA-256("fat32|disk_number|device_id|partition_start_lba|partition_size_lba|label")

This keeps re-runs reproducible for the same exact plan.

Verification contract

Owned FAT32 formatter is not complete unless it verifies its own writes.

Verify-after-write checks

Immediately after writing, re-open raw disk and verify:

MBR

signature 0x55AA

one primary partition present

type = 0x0C

start LBA matches plan

size LBA matches plan

FAT32 boot sector

jump instruction valid

OEM field present

bytes/sector = 512

sectors/cluster = expected

reserved sector count = expected

FAT count = 2

total sectors = expected

FAT size = expected

root cluster = 2

FSInfo sector number matches plan

backup boot sector number matches plan

boot signature 0x55AA

FSInfo

lead signature valid

structure signature valid

trailing signature valid

free cluster and next free fields acceptable

Backup boot sector

present and matches primary boot sector where required

FAT regions

FAT#1 and FAT#2 exist

cluster 0/1 reserved entries valid

root cluster chain initialized correctly

Root directory

cluster 2 readable

volume label entry valid if written

Verify token

Success token:

FAT32_VERIFY_OK

Failure token examples:

FAT32_VERIFY_FAIL:MBR_SIGNATURE

FAT32_VERIFY_FAIL:PARTITION_TYPE

FAT32_VERIFY_FAIL:BOOT_BPS

FAT32_VERIFY_FAIL:FSINFO_SIGNATURE

FAT32_VERIFY_FAIL:FAT_MIRROR

FAT32_VERIFY_FAIL:ROOT_CLUSTER

Receipt schema requirements

Extend your current storage.receipt.v1 discipline with owned formatter fields.

Plan receipt

Action:

plan-format-fat32-owned

Fields:

